2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20most%20common%20monthly%20bills%20are%20just%20part%20of%20the%20picture%20for%20many%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20bills%20are%20just%20one%20piece%20of%20the%20picture%20showing%20the%20current%20cost%20of%20living.%20Khalfani-Cox%20noted%20that%20there%20are%20monthly%20expenses%20that%20don't%20come%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20single%20bill%20but%20still%20have%20an%20immense%20impact%20on%20a%20household's%20finances%2C%20like%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThings%20like%20credit%20card%20bills%2C%20student%20loans%2C%20and%20even%20buy%20now%20pay%20later%20obligations%20increasingly%20consume%20a%20big%20chunk%20of%20people's%20budgets%2C%26quot%3B%20Khalfani-Cox%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20pointed%20to%20escalating%20food%20prices%20and%20inflation%20at%20the%20grocery%20store.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%20inflation%20peaked%20at%20a%20year-over-year%20rate%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E9.1%25%20in%20June%202022.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fviral-6-to-1-grocery-method-tiktok-budgeting-will-coleman-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20at%20home%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20(i.e.%20food%20you%20bring%20home%20from%20the%20grocery%20store)%20were%20hit%20even%20harder%2C%20reaching%2013.5%25%20in%20August%20of%20the%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20that%20number%20was%20just%201.0%25%20in%20February%2C%20we%20are%20not%20seeing%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-inflation-goods-durables-deflation-groceries-expensive-federal-reserve-cars-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edeflation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20we%20are%20starting%20to%20see%20in%20other%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faverage-cost-monthly-household-bills-change-pandemic-covid-rent-mortgage-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22