y%20month%20for%20a%20loan%20tied%20to%20the%20same%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20observers%20miss%20a%20crucial%20point%2C%20though%3A%20When%20rates%20fall%2C%20%3Cem%3Edemand%20%3C%2Fem%3Eshoots%20up.%20Buyers%20flood%20back%20into%20the%20market%2C%20adding%20to%20the%20competition%20and%20possibly%20driving%20up%20prices.%20Over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20there's%20been%20a%20clear%20correlation%20between%20mortgage%20rates%20and%20inventory%3A%20When%20mortgage%20rates%20fall%2C%20the%20number%20of%20available%20homes%20for%20sale%20at%20a%20given%20moment%20shrinks.%20And%20when%20rates%20go%20up%2C%20more%20homes%20sit%20on%20the%20market%20and%20inventory%20rises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20borrowing%20rates%20do%20end%20up%20falling%20this%20year%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwill-mortgage-rates-go-down-in-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20predict%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20could%20trigger%20bidding%20wars%20and%20the%20kind%20of%20frenzied%20dealmaking%20that%20defined%20the%20pandemic-era%20housing%20boom.%20So%20while%20it%20may%20be%20uncomfortable%20right%20now%2C%20there's%20a%20good%20chance%20that%20buyers'%20prospects%20won't%20be%20getting%20better%20anytime%20soon%20%E2%80%94%20in%20fact%2C%20they%20could%20get%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20expect%20that%20lower%20rates%20are%20going%20to%20suddenly%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20you%20as%20a%20homebuyer%2C%26quot%3B%20Mike%20Simonsen%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20real-estate%20data%20firm%20Altos%20Research%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20see%20that%20the%20demand%20comes%20back%20in%20quickly%2C%20the%20competition%20heats%20up.%20Then%20we're%20right%20back%20into%20the%20bidding%20wars%20with%20low%20inventory%20and%20all%20of%20those%20challenges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBasically%2C%20it%20might%20be%20a%20better%20time%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20than%20you%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20prospective%20buyers%2C%20the%20lure%20of%20playing%20the%20waiting%20game%20comes%20down%20to%20basic%20math.%20Let's%20say%20you%20try%20to%20buy%20a%20%24400%2C000%20house%20with%20a%2020%25%20down%20payment%20and%20a%2030-year%20loan.%20The%20typical%20rate%20for%20that%20mortgage%20sits%20around%206.87%25%2C%20according%20to%20Freddie%20Mac%2C%20but%20maybe%20you%20have%20good%20credit%20and%20an%20enterprising%20loan%20officer%20who%20can%20get%20you%20a%206.5%25%20rate.%20Even%20under%20those%20generous%20terms%2C%20you're%20looking%20at%20a%20monthly%20payment%20of%20roughly%20%242%2C023.%20Compare%20that%20to%20the%20roughly%20two-thirds%20of%20American%20homeowners%20who%20are%20sitting%20on%20a%20mortgage%20with%20a%20rate%20below%204%25.%20Even%20at%20the%20top%20of%20that%20range%2C%20a%204%25%20mortgage%20on%20the%20same%20house%20would%20mean%20monthly%20payments%20of%20%241%2C528%20%E2%80%94%20a%20nearly%20%24500%20difference.%20You're%20not%20getting%20anything%20extra%20for%20that%20money%3B%20you're%20just%20not%20as%20lucky%20as%20someone%20who%20got%20a%20loan%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20So%2C%20yes%2C%20waiting%20it%20out%20until%20mortgage%20rates%20decline%20sure%20seems%20appealing.%20The%20disconnect%20comes%20in%20thinking%20that%20things%20will%20magically%20get%20better%20for%20buyers%20if%20and%20when%20that%20happens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20how%20sluggish%20the%20market%20gets%2C%20there%20are%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20American%20households%20looking%20to%20change%20their%20living%20situations%20at%20any%20given%20time%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%3A%20marriage%2C%20divorce%2C%20better%20schools%2C%20or%20new%20jobs.%20What%20matters%20is%20the%20balance%20between%20the%20number%20of%20buyers%20and%20sellers%3A%20When%20demand%20dwarfs%20supply%2C%20we%20get%20the%20pandemic%20housing%20boom.%20And%20if%20buyers%20pull%20back%2C%20homes%20sit%20longer%20or%20sellers%20drop%20their%20prices.%20That's%20why%20active%20inventory%20is%20so%20important%3A%20When%20buyers%20have%20more%20options%2C%20they%20can%20slow%20down%2C%20fully%20vet%20their%20choices%2C%20and%20maybe%20even%20haggle%20on%20the%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20because%20there's%20more%20movement%2C%20however%2C%20doesn't%20mean%20there's%20more%20active%20inventory.%20In%202021%2C%20a%20notoriously%20cutthroat%20year%20for%20house%20hunters%2C%20the%20number%20of%20sales%20reached%20the%20highest%20point%20in%20more%20than%2015%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.corelogic.com%2Fintelligence%2F2021-a-record-breaking-year-for-real-estate-transactions%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAt%2520the%2520end%2520of%25202021%2Cunits%2520sold%2520exceeded%25207%2520million.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoreLogic%3C%2Fa%3E%20found.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20number%20of%20homes%20on%20the%20market%20was%20hitting%20record%20lows.%20Even%20in%20the%20busy%20spring%20selling%20season%2C%20when%20you'd%20expect%20to%20see%20more%20than%201%20million%20single-family%20homes%20and%20condos%20on%20the%20market%20at%20any%20given%20time%2C%20there%20were%20less%20than%20500%2C000.%20Almost%20as%20soon%20as%20a%20listing%20hit%20the%20market%2C%20it%20was%20gone%20%E2%80%94%20scooped%20up%20by%20investors%2C%20cash-rich%20retirees%2C%20or%20first-time%20buyers%20who%20were%20either%20lucky%2C%20desperate%2C%20or%20both.%20This%20explains%20why%20many%20frustrated%20homebuyers%20shared%20a%20similar%20sentiment%20during%20the%20pandemic%3A%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20seems%20to%20be%20buying%20and%20selling%20homes%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20there%20are%20any%20out%20there%20for%20%3Cem%3Eme%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20mortgage%20rates%20start%20to%20make%20their%20way%20back%20down%2C%20a%20similar%20situation%20could%20play%20out.%20As%20of%20February%2C%20there%20were%20about%20665%2C000%20active%20listings%20across%20the%20country%2C%20according%20to%20Redfin%20%E2%80%94%20an%20increase%20of%2013%25%20from%20the%20year%20before%2C%20but%20well%20below%20the%20more%20than%201%20million%20homes%20on%20the%20market%20during%20the%20same%20month%20in%202018%20and%202019.%20And%20plenty%20of%20buyers%20are%20biding%20their%20time%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%2060%25%20of%20potential%20buyers%20said%20they%20were%20willing%20to%20wait%20for%20prices%20or%20rates%20to%20fall%20before%20buying%20a%20home%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.bankofamerica.com%2Fcontent%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2F2023%2F12%2Fbofa-report-shows-fewer-prospective-homebuyers-willing-to-wait-f.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20last%20year%20by%20Bank%20of%20America%20found.%20And%20as%20rates%20fall%2C%20more%20buyers%20are%20able%20to%20make%20the%20numbers%20work%3A%20For%20every%20percentage-point%20drop%20in%20mortgage%20rates%2C%20another%205%20million%20households%20are%20able%20to%20qualify%20for%20a%20%24400%2C000%20mortgage%2C%20according%20to%20estimates%20from%20John%20Burns%20Research%20and%20Consulting.%20So%20if%20you%20think%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20more%20housing%20inventory%20when%20rates%20fall%2C%20you're%20basically%20betting%20that%20the%20number%20of%20homes%20hitting%20the%20market%20would%20outpace%20all%20of%20that%20newly%20created%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20don't%20see%20that%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20Alex%20Thomas%2C%20a%20senior%20research%20analyst%20at%20JBREC%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20too%20many%20people%20that%20have%20been%20priced%20out%20that%20are%20waiting%20on%20the%20sidelines.%20I%20think%20that%20would%20overwhelm%20any%20increase%20in%20inventory%20that%20you'd%20see.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20in%20borrowing%20rates%20since%20mid-2022%20has%20kept%20as%20many%20as%201.33%20million%20home%20sales%20from%20happening%2C%20according%20to%20estimates%20from%20a%20recent%20working%20paper%20published%20by%20the%20Federal%20Housing%20Finance%20Agency.%20But%20a%20lot%20of%20those%20phantom%20sellers%20would%20also%20need%20to%20turn%20around%20and%20buy%20another%20home%2C%20meaning%20they're%20not%20actually%20adding%20to%20active%20inventory.%20And%20even%20if%20typical%20mortgage%20rates%20fall%20to%206%25%20or%205.5%25%20%E2%80%94%20a%20significant%20drop%20from%20the%20prevailing%20rate%20of%20nearly%207%25%20%E2%80%94%20there%20would%20still%20be%20people%20locked%20in%2C%20Will%20Doerner%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20FHFA%2C%20told%20me.%20That%20effect%20isn't%20going%20away%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20still%20going%20to%20have%20people%20who%20are%20not%20going%20to%20move%2C%20who%20are%20not%20going%20to%20give%20up%20their%20house%20forever%2C%20basically%2C%26quot%3B%20Doerner%20told%20me%2C%20referring%20to%20homeowners%20with%20mortgages%20below%204%25%20or%20even%203%25.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20take%20a%20heck%20of%20a%20change%20for%20them%20to%20ever%20want%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20those%20mortgages.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20alternative%20presents%20other%20complications%2C%20though%3A%20If%20mortgage%20rates%20remain%20stable%20or%20even%20rise%2C%20buyers%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20as%20much%20house%20as%20they%20could%20have%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20They're%20simply%20not%20getting%20as%20much%20bang%20for%20their%20buck.%20If%20they%20can%20adjust%20their%20expectations%20and%20still%20buy%20a%20home%2C%20though%2C%20they%20would%20trade%20the%20pain%20of%20today's%20higher%20payments%20for%20the%20benefits%20of%20getting%20on%20the%20homeownership%20ladder.%20One%20day%2C%20they%20might%20even%20break%20up%20with%20that%20mortgage%20rate%20and%20refinance%20for%20a%20better%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20buy%20a%20smaller%20home%2C%20but%20I%20still%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20buy%20a%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20Simonsen%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWhereas%20when%20it's%20crazy%20hot%2C%20I%20can't%20even%