%3Cp%3EThat%20way%2C%20everyone%20can%20avoid%20an%20awkward%20dietary%20conversation%20at%20the%20table.%20Such%20luxurious%20events%20should%20already%20account%20for%20any%20special%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDO%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EPractice%20the%20continental%20way%20of%20eating.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrying-a-1000-royal-etiquette-class-at-the-plaza-hotel-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinental%20dining%20style%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20considered%20common%20ground%20for%20people%20from%20different%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20%26quot%3Bholding%20the%20fork%20in%20the%20left%20hand%20and%20knife%20in%20the%20right%20hand%20without%20switching%C2%A0them%20back%20and%20forth%20as%20you%20would%20do%20in%20American-style%20eating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20typically%20use%20their%20knives%20and%20forks%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bzig-zag%26quot%3B%20way%2C%20said%20Musayeva%2C%20but%20that's%20seen%20as%20informal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDON'T%3A%20Take%20a%20sip%20of%20your%20drink%20before%20you've%20finished%20chewing.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20one%20is%20pretty%20simple%3A%20take%20small%20bites%20of%20your%20food%20and%20finish%20chewing%20and%20swallowing%20before%20you%20drink%20your%20beverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDO%3A%20Leave%20your%20big%20handbag%20in%20the%20coat%20closet.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20room%20at%20the%20table%20of%20esteemed%20guests%20for%20your%20bulky%20shoulder%20bag%2C%20so%20it's%20best%20to%20leave%20it%20at%20coat%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you'd%20rather%20not%20ditch%20your%20belongings%2C%20Musayeva%20suggests%20accessorizing%20with%20a%20smaller%20purse%20that%20fits%20in%20your%20lap%20when%20it's%20time%20for%20dinner%20to%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20recommend%20always%20to%20take%20a%20clutch%20or%20a%20small%20black%20bag%20that%20you%20can%20then%20place%20in%20your%20lap%20and%20cover%20it%20with%20a%20napkin%2C%26quot%3B%20Musayeva%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDON'T%3A%20Introduce%20your%20VIP%20guest%20%3Cem%3Eto%20%3C%2Fem%3Esomeone.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20first%20impressions%2C%20you%20should%20always%20make%20sure%20the%20VIP's%20status%20is%20discreetly%20acknowledged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20such%2C%20you%20should%20never%20introduce%20them%20%3Cem%3Eto%20%3C%2Fem%3Esomeone%20%E2%80%94%20everyone%20should%20already%20know%20who%20they%20are%2C%20so%20it's%20unnecessary.%20Instead%2C%20Musayeva%20said%2C%20you%20should%20introduce%20people%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20say%20this%20formula%3A%20'May%20I%20introduce%20to%20you'%26quot%3B%20and%20then%20the%20name%2C%20Musayeva%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDO%3A%20Let%20the%20VIP%20guest%20decide%20when%20to%20shake%20hands.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20want%20to%20make%20an%20honored%20guest%20feel%20welcomed%20by%20extending%20a%20hand%20to%20them%20as%20a%20greeting.%20But%2C%20Musayeva%20said%2C%20that's%20not%20the%20proper%20way%20to%20go%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20hierarchical%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20most%20important%20person%20has%20to%20give%20permission%20to%20a%20less%20important%20person%20to%20shake%20their%20hand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDON'T%3A%20Order%20your%20own%20drink%20at%20the%20dinner%20table.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20formal%20dinners%2C%20drink%20pairings%20are%20usually%20predetermined%20to%20match%20the%20food%20on%20the%20menu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20come%20off%20as%20rude%20if%20you%20object%20to%20the%20wine%20or%20other%20drink%20chosen%20by%20your%20host%20or%20chef%2C%20Musayeva%20said.%20It's%20better%20to%20trust%20their%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECocktail%20hour%20is%20the%20best%20time%20to%20order%20whatever%20beverage%20you're%20craving%2C%20but%20that%20ends%20once%20you%20sit%20down%20for%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDO%3A%20Whatever%20it%20takes%20to%20fit%20in.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3